To validate a NeXus hdf/xml file against a "default schema" use e.g.

    nxvalidate --path /home/faa59/nexus-definitions/schema  NXmonopd.hdf

--path specifies the location of the generated NeXus xsd schema files

To instead validate a file via the web with "default schema" use

    nxvalidate -w NXmonopd.hdf

If an NXentry has a <definition> field, this will be used to validate it, otherwise the generic NXentry.xsd will be used

If you wish to only use the generic NXentry.xsd instead of and <definition> specified one, use the  -n option

    nxvalidate -w -n NXmonopd.hdf

To validate all NXentry in a file against a specific definition use the -d option e.g.

    nxvalidate -w -d NXmonopd NXmonopd.hdf      # force NXmonopd.xsd

